@Comment:	the transcript has only tape1side1 and tape2side2, missing tape1side2 and tape2side1. This means it skips ~4300 lines from 2422 to 6719 in the audio. The last utterance is also untranscribed
@Comment:	MLU 1.04 the majority of it. Morpheme utterances were imitations of an immediately preceding utterance, spontaneous 2 morpheme utterances included "blocks" and "fix it" and "go down".
@Situation:	Playing. The interaction took place almost entirely in the living room which has a large picture window overlooking Morningside Park.
@Activities:	Peter crawling, pretending to swim, down hall to living room where Patsy and Lois wait
@Comment:	Peter was mostly interested in his own blocks and in his book "Pat the Bunny," the slides, the seesaw and the tape recorder. He also enjoyed running to the window and standing on the sill to look for things he could hear like fire engines and dogs. Peter's mother was at home and not in the room during the sessions. Peter gets along well without her presence. He paid no attention to Jennifer except to comment when she cried.
@Tape Location:	Tape 1, side 1
@Types:	long, toyplay, TD

@Comment:	This is tapes 5, 6, and 7. The only problem is that tape 5 is replaced with 6 at 3600 which results in a few untranscribed lines until 3618.
@Situation:	Playing-in-living+room
@Comment:	Peter talked much more at this session than at Session02 producing over 300 different comprehensible utterances. He was still very much fascinated by the tape recorder and also spent much time playing with his blocks. At the end of the first session Father came home and there was some active play accompanied mostly by adult. Among the most frequent words occuring at this time were kaka (car) , more broken , house (playing with blocks) , turn it (watching the tape recorder) , turn around (watching tape recorder or spinning himself around) , open (RE: tape recorder) , fix , there , put on it , button (tape recorder) , close (tape recorder).

@Comment:	MLU 1.04 the majority of it. Morpheme utterances were imitations of an immediately preceding utterance, spontaneous 2 morpheme utterances included "blocks" and "fix it" and "go down".
@Situation:	Playing. The interaction took place almost entirely in the living room which has a large picture window overlooking Morningside Park.
@Activities:	Peter crawling, pretending to swim, down hall to living room where Patsy and Lois wait
@Comment:	Peter was mostly interested in his own blocks and in his book "Pat the Bunny," the slides, the seesaw and the tape recorder. He also enjoyed running to the window and standing on the sill to look for things he could hear like fire engines and dogs. Peter's mother was at home and not in the room during the sessions. Peter gets along well without her presence. He paid no attention to Jennifer except to comment when she cried.

@Languages:	eng
@Participants:	CHI Target_Child, PAT Investigator, LOI Investigator, MOT Mother, FAT Father
@Options:	multi
@ID:	eng|Bloom|CHI|1;10.11|male|TD||Target_Child|||
@ID:	eng|Bloom|PAT|||||Investigator|||

@ID:	eng|Bloom|MOT||female|||Mother|||
@ID:	eng|Bloom|FAT||male|||Father|||
@Media:	011011, audio
@Date:	08-NOV-1971
@Comment:	MLU 1.37
@Tape Location:	Tape 5 , side 1 , 035
@Comment:	This is tapes 5, 6, and 7. The only problem is that tape 5 is replaced with 6 at 3600 which results in a few untranscribed lines until 3618.
@Situation:	Playing-in-living+room
@Comment:	Peter talked much more at this session than at Session02 producing over 300 different comprehensible utterances. He was still very much fascinated by the tape recorder and also spent much time playing with his blocks. At the end of the first session Father came home and there was some active play accompanied mostly by adult. Among the most frequent words occuring at this time were kaka (car) , more broken , house (playing with blocks) , turn it (watching the tape recorder) , turn around (watching tape recorder or spinning himself around) , open (RE: tape recorder) , fix , there , put on it , button (tape recorder) , close (tape recorder).
@Types:	long, toyplay, TD
